---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Research" sideBarActiveItemID="research">
  <div class="pb-12 mt-5">

    <h2 style="font-family:'Cormorant Garamond',serif;font-size:40px;font-weight:300;color:#1C1917;letter-spacing:-0.01em;line-height:1.1;margin-bottom:48px;">Research</h2>

    <!-- Working Papers -->
    <div style="margin-bottom:44px;">
      <span class="section-label">Working Papers</span>
      <div style="border-top:1px solid #E8E2D9;">
        <div class="entry-row">
          <div style="display:flex;align-items:baseline;gap:12px;flex-wrap:wrap;">
            <a href="https://paths2include.eu/publications/gender-norms-and-parents-employment-characteristics-in-europe/" target="_blank" style="font-family:'Lora',serif;font-size:17px;font-weight:500;color:#7D2035;text-decoration:none;border-bottom:1px solid rgba(125,32,53,0.32);line-height:1.55;">
              Gender norms and parents' employment characteristics in Europe
            </a>
            <button class="abstract-btn" data-target="abstract-paper1">Abstract ↓</button>
          </div>
          <p style="font-family:'Lora',serif;font-size:14px;color:#6B6460;margin-top:8px;font-style:italic;">with Sara Ayllón</p>
          <div id="abstract-paper1" class="abstract-panel">
            <!-- Replace this with your abstract text -->
            Parenthood penalises women and rewards men in the labour market, yet the cultural forces behind this asymmetry remain poorly understood. This paper studies the extent to which gender norms shape not only whether parents work, but how, examining eleven labour market outcomes for mothers and fathers across 31 European countries. We merge individual-level data from the European Union Labour Force Survey (EU-LFS) with cohort-level data from the Integrated Values Survey (IVS) on the gender norm progressivity of previous generations, and instrument regional norm progressivity with a religiosity index constructed for the same grandmother cohort. For mothers, progressive norms expand access to flexible arrangements but do not close the employment gap relative to childless women. For fathers, progressive norms weaken breadwinner pressure, reducing precarious overwork and defensive employment choices, while simultaneously promoting job quality.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Work in Progress -->
    <div style="margin-bottom:44px;">
      <span class="section-label">Work in Progress</span>
      <div style="border-top:1px solid #E8E2D9;">
        <div class="entry-row">
          <p style="font-family:'Cormorant Garamond',serif;font-size:17px;font-weight:500;color:#1C1917;line-height:1.55;max-width:640px;">
            Unpacking the null impact of paternity leave extensions on fertility and labour market outcomes
          </p>
          <p style="font-family:'Lora',serif;font-size:14px;color:#6B6460;margin-top:8px;font-style:italic;">with Sara Ayllón</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Participation in Projects -->
    <div>
      <span class="section-label">Participation in Projects</span>
      <div style="border-top:1px solid #E8E2D9;">

        <div class="entry-row">
          <p style="font-family:'Cormorant Garamond',serif;font-size:17px;font-weight:500;color:#1C1917;line-height:1.55;max-width:640px;">
            Paternity leave reforms in Spain: Impacts on fertility and labour market outcomes
          </p>
          <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:3px;">
            <p style="font-family:'Lora',serif;font-size:13px;color:#6B6460;">Funding entity: Women Institute, Spanish Ministry of Equality</p>
            <p style="font-family:'Lora',serif;font-size:13px;color:#6B6460;">PI: <a href="http://www.saraayllon.eu/" target="_blank" style="color:#7D2035;text-decoration:none;border-bottom:1px solid rgba(125,32,53,0.32);">Sara Ayllón</a></p>
            <p style="font-family:monospace;font-size:9px;color:#7D2035;letter-spacing:0.1em;text-transform:uppercase;margin-top:4px;">2024–2025</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="entry-row">
          <p style="font-family:'Cormorant Garamond',serif;font-size:17px;font-weight:500;color:#1C1917;line-height:1.55;max-width:640px;">
            Reformas del permiso de paternidad en España: impacto sobre la fecundidad y la actividad laboral
          </p>
          <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:3px;">
            <p style="font-family:'Lora',serif;font-size:13px;color:#6B6460;">Funding entity: Institute of Fiscal Studies</p>
            <p style="font-family:'Lora',serif;font-size:13px;color:#6B6460;">PI: <a href="http://www.saraayllon.eu/" target="_blank" style="color:#7D2035;text-decoration:none;border-bottom:1px solid rgba(125,32,53,0.32);">Sara Ayllón</a></p>
            <p style="font-family:monospace;font-size:9px;color:#7D2035;letter-spacing:0.1em;text-transform:uppercase;margin-top:4px;">2024–2025</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="entry-row">
          <p style="font-family:'Cormorant Garamond',serif;font-size:17px;font-weight:500;color:#1C1917;line-height:1.55;max-width:640px;">
            <a href="https://paths2include.eu/" target="_blank" style="color:#7D2035;text-decoration:none;border-bottom:1px solid rgba(125,32,53,0.32);">PATHS2INCLUDE</a>: European labour markets under pressure — New knowledge on pathways to include persons in vulnerable situations
          </p>
          <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:3px;">
            <p style="font-family:'Lora',serif;font-size:13px;color:#6B6460;">Funding entity: Horizon Europe, European Commission</p>
            <p style="font-family:'Lora',serif;font-size:13px;color:#6B6460;">PI: <a href="http://www.saraayllon.eu/" target="_blank" style="color:#7D2035;text-decoration:none;border-bottom:1px solid rgba(125,32,53,0.32);">Sara Ayllón</a></p>
            <p style="font-family:monospace;font-size:9px;color:#7D2035;letter-spacing:0.1em;text-transform:uppercase;margin-top:4px;">2024–2029</p>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>

  </div>

  <script>
    document.querySelectorAll('.abstract-btn').forEach(btn => {
      btn.addEventListener('click', () => {
        const targetId = btn.getAttribute('data-target');
        if (!targetId) return;
        const panel = document.getElementById(targetId);
        if (!panel) return;
        const isOpen = panel.classList.contains('open');
        panel.classList.toggle('open');
        btn.textContent = isOpen ? 'Abstract ↓' : 'Abstract ↑';
      });
    });
  </script>

</BaseLayout>
